Godwin Isenyo, Kaduna The Commissioner for Human Services and Social Development in Kaduna State, Hajiya Hafsat Baba, on Wednesday said  Governor Nasir El-Rufai would  present  a memo on Almajiri  to his northern counterparts. Baba said the memo to the 19 northern state governors contained a practical steps to halt the Almajiri menace in the North. The commissioner  said this during a meeting with stakeholders working on the Almajiri menace in the state, describing it as “time bomb.” She  said the  El-Rufai  administration had got the political will to address the menace. She said all that was needed was  the cooperation of other states regarding  the  inter-state movement of the children. Baba was unhappy with  parents forcing  their children  to be in the streets. According to her, the law banning street begging and hawking in the state will be implemented to check the development. Copyright PUNCH.
